burn(address,uint256).details: Burn tokens from a specific address (owner only)

params.amount: The amount of tokens to burn
params.from: The address to burn tokens from

burnBatch(address[],uint256[]).details: Burn tokens from multiple addresses in a batch (owner only)

params.from: Array of addresses to burn tokens from

mint(address,uint256).details: Mint tokens to a specific address

params.amount: The amount of tokens to mint
params.to: The address to mint tokens to

mintBatch(address[],uint256[]).details: Mint tokens to multiple addresses in a batch

params.amounts: Array of amounts to mint for each token ID
params.to: Array of addresses to mint tokens to

mintSingleBatch(address[]).details: Mint 1 token to multiple addresses in a batch

params.to: Array of addresses to mint 1 token to

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

setTransferable(bool).details: Toggles the transferability of the NFTs

setURI(string).details: Set a new URI for the contract

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

uri(uint256).details: See {IERC1155MetadataURI-uri}. This implementation returns the same URI for *all* token types. It relies on the token type ID substitution mechanism https://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/eip-1155#metadata[defined in the EIP]. Clients calling this function must replace the `\{id\}` substring with the actual token type ID.
